{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed methodology is validated on a complex district heating system benchmark, demonstrating that the Mahalanobis distance-based combination rule outperforms both fixed and output-dependent weighting strategies in terms of economic performance and constraint satisfaction.",
    "Furthermore, the proposed MHE-based observer significantly enhances state estimation accuracy compared to an open-loop approach, leading to improved overall closedloop performance.",
    "Future work will focus on integrating the proposed framework within an active learning setting to leverage MPC for informative data acquisition.Fig. 1:1Fig.",
    "1: Schematic representation of the AROMA DHS and its variables.",
    "Fig. 2:2Fig."
  ]
}